Philippine GSIS Scraps Global Investment Program, Inquirer Says

-- B y   C e c i l i a   Y a p
-- 
2011-04-06T23:34:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-06/philippine-gsis-scraps-global-investment-program-inquirer-says.html
Philippine state pension fund
Government Service Insurance System will bring back to the
country its entire $670 million overseas investment portfolio
after returns fell below the minimum target, Philippine Daily
Inquirer reported, citing an unidentified source.  The pension fund believes local assets could be more
lucrative without it having to take foreign exchange risks,
Inquirer said, citing its source. GSIS  will give its offshore
fund managers two months to unwind the investment, the report
said  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Cecilia Yap at 
 cyap19@bloomberg.net  